case_circumstances:
On 12-24-2010, the remains of a badly decomposed human body was found on a levee within the Eastshore State Park in Richmond, CA.  The autopsy reveled the deceased suffered severe internal injuries, with no visible exterior injuries (consistent with falling/jumping from an unknown height).  The only clothing recovered was a brown "D" width Stuart McGuire Chukka Style Boot, with velcro straps, black ribbed socks and a Seiko wrist watch with a black nylon buckle style band.
The deceased appears to be a white male adult, 40 t0 60 years-old, 5'-7" tall, 142 pounds,  He had extensive gold dental work and a stint in the left anterior descending artery.  He also has what appears to be a faded small tattoo on his back.
